The global optical preclinical imaging market is segmented based on products, modality, and applications. In terms of products, the market is categorized into imaging systems, reagents, and software. The imaging systems segment is expected to dominate the market due to the increasing demand for advanced imaging technologies. On the basis of modality, the market is further classified into optical bioluminescence/ fluorescence imaging systems, standalone fluorescence imaging systems, planar illumination systems, and Cerenkov luminescence imaging systems. The optical bioluminescence/ fluorescence imaging systems segment is anticipated to witness significant growth owing to their superior imaging capabilities. By application, the market is segmented into cancer cell research, pharmacokinetics & pharmacodynamics studies, bio distribution studies, longitudinal therapeutic efficacy monitoring, and epigenetics, with cancer cell research being the leading application segment.

